// Create a logical device } void Renderer::createSurface() { // Create the surface } void Renderer::createSwapchain() { // Create swapchain and swapchain images } void Renderer::createImageViews() { // Create image views for swapchain images } void Renderer::createRenderPass() { // Create render pass } void Renderer::createGraphicsPipeline() { // Create graphics pipeline } void Renderer::createFramebuffers() { // Create framebuffers for swapchain images } void Renderer::createCommandPool() { // Create command pool } void Renderer::createCommandBuffers() { // Create and record command buffers } void Renderer::createSynchronizationObjects() { // Create semaphores and fences for synchronization } \`\`\` This outline provides a basic structure for the Renderer class's CPP file. You would need to complete each function with the appropriate Vulkan, GLFW, and GLM calls. It is necessary to familiarize yourself with these libraries' concepts, such as creating Vulkan objects and synchronizing various components. To explore how to properly implement these functions, consult the official Vulkan documentation and samples: https://vulkan-tutorial.com/"},{"instruction":"hello","output":"Hello! How can I assist you today?"},{"instruction":"what is actual league in Path of exile","output":"In Path of Exile, \\"actual league\\" refers to the current league or challenge league that is active at the time. These leagues are periodically released by the game's developers and usually last for approximately three months, after which a new league is released. Each league has a unique set of mechanics, content, and challenges, making it distinct from the game's permanent standard league. Players can create a new character for each league to experience the content and compete in its challenges."},{"instruction":"name me three last league","output":"Sure, the last three Path of Exile leagues were: 1. Ultimatum (April 2021 - July 2021) - This league introduced the Trialmaster, a new NPC who ch